 LAGOS – Justice Sylvester Popnen of a Rivers State High Court sitting in Port Harcourt has adjourned till June 17 for the arraignment of four persons in alleged connection with the robbery and murder of one Chidi Onwukwe, in Elelenwo, Port Harcourt. The charge marked PHC/667/CR/2022 filed by the Police named the alleged the four suspects as Samuel Onwukwe, 49, (1st defendant); Andrew Epai Otanye, 27, (2nd defendant); Samuel Emmason, 26, (3rd defendant) and Prom­ise George, 30, (4th defendant). Justice Popnen fixed the date following the suspects’ absence. When the matter was called, police counsel, Essien Edet, informed the court that only Samuel was in custody but that the Investigative Po­lice Officer (IPO) in the case, who should have brought him to court, was away on a special duty He added that others had yet to be served the charge and were not in court to take their pleas. “The 1st defendant is in police custody but the IPO is in Bayelsa on a special as­signment. We are asking for adjournment to enable the defendants to appear to take plea,” Mr. Edet added. While the 1st to 3rd defen­dants had no legal represen­tation, the 4th defendant was represented by J. Okpamen. POLL Justice Popnen directed the prosecutor to ensure the defendants were served to en­able them appear in court to take their pleas The judge adjourned pro­ceedings till June 17.